# Bug Fixes

## 1. Fix family tree silently truncating data at 1000 relationships

**File:** [app/dashboard/members/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Project/mine/giapha-os/app/dashboard/members/page.tsx)

**Problem:** PostgREST has a default `max-rows` cap of 1000. The app fetched `relationships` in a single request, silently capping at 1000 rows. For a genealogy app with many members, relationships beyond row 1000 were never loaded, causing child nodes to disappear from the tree.

**Fix:** Replace the single fetch with a paginated loop that fetches in 1000-row batches until all rows are loaded. Applied to both `persons` and `relationships`.

```ts
const persons: Person[] = [];
let pFrom = 0;
while (true) {
  const { data } = await supabase
    .from("persons").select("*")
    .order("birth_year", { ascending: true, nullsFirst: false })
    .range(pFrom, pFrom + 999);
  if (!data || data.length === 0) break;
  persons.push(...(data as Person[]));
  if (data.length < 1000) break;
  pFrom += 1000;
}
// same pattern for relationships
```

> **Note for self-hosted deployments:** You can also increase the PostgREST cap via the `PGRST_DB_MAX_ROWS` environment variable in `docker-compose.yml`, but the pagination approach is recommended as it scales without a ceiling.
